reviews.text: Good place to relax. Nice atmosphere and comfortable seating. Breakfast was very tasty with omelet, toast, grapefruit juice and coffee. Portion size was quite large and the juice was fresh squeezed, pulp and all. Great stop for any meal in Midlevels.

Had dinner here with some colleagues. The appetizer is amazing -- fitting for the name, anything meat related was utterly mind-blowing. Unfortunately, I had pasta and another colleague had a veggie burger that was so-so.

Forewarning, it was extremely stuffy inside, despite the staff fiddling with the gigantic fan/cooling system. By the end of our dinner, we legitimately was unfortunately swimming a bit in our sweat. Pick your tables carefully!

Your morning staff are fabulous. They had my coffee ready before I even ordered it this morning. 
I'm happy for the rest of the day now 😊

An attractive enticing deal for steak, fries, salad and wine, but somewhat disappointing meat.
Great staff, salad and ambience let down by beef that was less Wagyu than I am.
The portion is reasonable,  but the chicken in the burger is dry and hard.

reviews.text: Service is terrible. Made a reservation for 9:30 and start calling you 3 times starting from 9pm, 9:15 and 9:25. Smells like sweat inside the restaurant. Waitress lose patient when getting our order. Soup is not hot but slightly warm. However pasta is hot.

They charge any guy that looks like a foreigner $300 HKD, but any guy who doesn't look like a foreigner (and white men) are free, which I find to be extremely racist. The bouncer as well said, "I hate tourists," but he was Indian?? I went inside for a bit and their music sucked. At least ladies are free.
Great location, restaurant during the day (food are server in the afternoon and at night) , and turn into a club after 11pm
Beer is hot. WTF
Nice, quiet location during the day. Pleasant staff and reasonably priced drinks. Great place to stop off for refreshments when you're exploring Hong Kong.
